Based on this issue [https://github.com/vuejs/vuex/issues/863](Issue), I was also struggling to apply a dynamic namespace to a component that could be used anywhere in the component tree. To support the namespace being applied to a component via the props, I added functionality for the namespace to be supplied as a function.

Example usage:
`
    var namespace_def = "settings/someModule/";

    module.exports = {
        props: [ "namespace" ],
        computed: mapState((self) => self.namespace || namespace_def, [
            'options', 
            'items'
        ]),
        methods: mapActions((self) => self.namespace || namespace_def, [
            'SomeAction', 
            'AnotherAction'
        ])
     };
`
